import json
import pathlib
import random 

from shiny import App, ui, render
from shinywidgets import output_widget, render_widget
from ipyleaflet import Map, CircleMarker, MarkerCluster,basemaps, GeoJSON, Popup
from ipywidgets import HTML
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from thedata import df


here = pathlib.Path(__file__)
with open(here.parent / "america.geo.json", "r") as f:
    country_boundaries = json.load(f)

def random_color(feature):
    return {
        "color": "black",
        "fillColor": random.choice(["red", "yellow", "green", "orange"]),
    }

# Define the UI
app_ui = ui.page_navbar(
    ui.nav_panel("Inicio",
        ui.layout_columns(
            ui.card(
                ui.card_header("Bienvenido"),
                ui.p("Este es un mapa interactivo que muestra los programas de prevención en Latinoamérica."),
                height="600px"
            )
        )
    ),
    ui.nav_panel("Mapa", 
        ui.layout_columns(
            ui.card(
                ui.card_header("Programas de prevención en Latinoamérica"),
                output_widget("mymap"),
                height="600px"
            )
        )
    ),
    title = "Programas"
)

def server(input, output, session):
   
    @output
    @render_widget
    def mymap():
        data = df
        data = data.replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan).dropna(subset=['lat', 'long'])

        # Create a map centered at the specified location
        m = Map(center=(-10.3601, -71.0589), zoom=2.5,
                basemap= basemaps.CartoDB.Positron)
        
        geo_json = GeoJSON(  
            data=country_boundaries,  
            style={  
                "opacity": 1,  
                "dashArray": "9",  
                "fillOpacity": 0.1,  
                "weight": 1,  
            },
           
            style_callback=random_color, 
        )  

        m.add_layer(geo_json)  
        
        

 
        


        return m

# Create the app
app = App(app_ui, server)

if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run()
